 ## Expected result
 
+Stdout (final):
 ```
 Saved /path/to/output.png
 ```
 
+Stderr (always, before stdout — quota line from Codex backend headers):
+```
+[Codex PRO] | 5h: 0% (resets in 4h48m) | 7d: 1% (resets in 6d16h)
+```
+
+The quota line is parsed from `x-codex-*` response headers exposed by the ChatGPT backend:
+
+| Header | Meaning |
+|--------|---------|
+| `x-codex-plan-type` | Account plan (e.g. `pro`, `plus`) |
+| `x-codex-active-limit` | Limit tier (`premium`, `standard`) |
+| `x-codex-primary-used-percent` | Short-window usage (default 5h / 300 min) |
+| `x-codex-primary-window-minutes` | Short window length |
+| `x-codex-primary-reset-after-seconds` | Seconds until short window resets |
+| `x-codex-secondary-used-percent` | Long-window usage (default 7d / 10080 min) |
+| `x-codex-secondary-window-minutes` | Long window length |
+| `x-codex-secondary-reset-after-seconds` | Seconds until long window resets |
+| `x-codex-credits-has-credits` / `-balance` / `-unlimited` | Add-on credit state |
+
+A ⚠ marker appears when either window crosses 80% used. Quota is also printed on `429`/HTTPError responses so you can see why a call was rejected.
+
 Exit code 0 on success, 1 if no `image_generation_call` result was found (re-run with `--events` to inspect the raw stream).
 
